### Auth API Test Suite
### Base URL
@baseUrl = http://localhost:4000/api/v1
@email = test@example.com
@password = Test@123

### ============================================
### 1. LOGIN - POST /auth/login
### ============================================

### Test 1.1: Successful Login
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "{{email}}",
  "password": "{{password}}"
}

### Test 1.2: Login with Missing Email
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "password": "{{password}}"
}

### Test 1.3: Login with Missing Password
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "{{email}}"
}

### Test 1.4: Login with Invalid Credentials
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "{{email}}",
  "password": "WrongPassword123"
}

### Test 1.5: Login with Non-existent User
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "nonexistent@example.com",
  "password": "{{password}}"
}

### ============================================
### 2. ME - GET /auth/me (Requires Authentication)
### ============================================

### Test 2.1: Get User Details with Valid Token
GET {{baseUrl}}/auth/me
Cookie: accessToken=YOUR_ACCESS_TOKEN; refreshToken=YOUR_REFRESH_TOKEN

### Test 2.2: Get User Details without Token
GET {{baseUrl}}/auth/me

### Test 2.3: Get User Details with Expired Access Token (should rotate)
GET {{baseUrl}}/auth/me
Cookie: accessToken=EXPIRED_TOKEN; refreshToken=YOUR_REFRESH_TOKEN

### Test 2.4: Get User Details with Invalid Token
GET {{baseUrl}}/auth/me
Cookie: accessToken=invalid_token; refreshToken=invalid_token

### ============================================
### 3. LOGOUT - POST /auth/logout (Requires Authentication)
### ============================================

### Test 3.1: Successful Logout
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/logout
Cookie: accessToken=YOUR_ACCESS_TOKEN; refreshToken=YOUR_REFRESH_TOKEN

### Test 3.2: Logout without Token
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/logout

### Test 3.3: Logout with Invalid Token
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/logout
Cookie: accessToken=invalid_token; refreshToken=invalid_token

### ============================================
### 4. RESET PASSWORD - POST /auth/reset-password/:email
### ============================================

### Test 4.1: Successful Password Reset
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/reset-password/{{email}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "oldPassword": "{{password}}",
  "newPassword": "NewTest@123"
}

### Test 4.2: Reset Password with Wrong Old Password
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/reset-password/{{email}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "oldPassword": "WrongPassword",
  "newPassword": "NewTest@123"
}

### Test 4.3: Reset Password for Non-existent User
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/reset-password/nonexistent@example.com
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "oldPassword": "{{password}}",
  "newPassword": "NewTest@123"
}

### Test 4.4: Reset Password with Missing Old Password
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/reset-password/{{email}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "newPassword": "NewTest@123"
}

### Test 4.5: Reset Password with Missing New Password
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/reset-password/{{email}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "oldPassword": "{{password}}"
}

### ============================================
### 5. TOKEN ROTATION TEST
### ============================================

### Test 5.1: Access Protected Route with Expired Access Token
### This should trigger automatic token rotation
GET {{baseUrl}}/auth/me
Cookie: accessToken=EXPIRED_ACCESS_TOKEN; refreshToken=VALID_REFRESH_TOKEN

### ============================================
### 6. COMPLETE FLOW TEST
### ============================================

### Step 1: Login
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "{{email}}",
  "password": "{{password}}"
}

### Step 2: Get User Details (copy cookies from login response)
GET {{baseUrl}}/auth/me
Cookie: accessToken=FROM_LOGIN; refreshToken=FROM_LOGIN

### Step 3: Reset Password
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/reset-password/{{email}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "oldPassword": "{{password}}",
  "newPassword": "NewTest@123"
}

### Step 4: Try to access with old token (should fail - tokens revoked)
GET {{baseUrl}}/auth/me
Cookie: accessToken=OLD_TOKEN; refreshToken=OLD_TOKEN

### Step 5: Login with new password
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "{{email}}",
  "password": "NewTest@123"
}

### Step 6: Logout
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/logout
Cookie: accessToken=FROM_NEW_LOGIN; refreshToken=FROM_NEW_LOGIN

### Step 7: Try to access after logout (should fail)
GET {{baseUrl}}/auth/me
Cookie: accessToken=FROM_LOGOUT; refreshToken=FROM_LOGOUT
